   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🧬 Project 2 — Biologically Grounded SNP Annotation\n",
    "### Linking GWAS & SHAP Top SNPs to Genes, Pathways and Known Flowering Biology\n",
    "**PhD Project — Prof. Agnieszka Golicz Lab, Wageningen University & Research**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Builds on:** Project 1 (GWAS + genomic prediction for Days to Flowering)  \n",
    "**New data added:** Faba bean reference genome annotation (Jayakodi, Golicz et al., Nature 2023)\n",
    "\n",
    "**What this notebook does:**\n",
    "1. Reload top GWAS SNPs and SHAP SNPs from Project 1\n",
    "2. Download the faba bean reference genome GFF3 annotation (Nature 2023)\n",
    "3. Find the nearest annotated gene to each top SNP (±100 kb window)\n",
    "4. Annotate genes with functional descriptions\n",
    "5. Cross-reference with known flowering-time genes (FT, SOC1, FLC, CO, AP1, TFL1, LFY)\n",
    "6. Run Gene Ontology (GO) enrichment on top SNP-proximal genes\n",
    "7. Visualise: SNP → gene → pathway connection\n",
    "\n",
    "**PhD duty addressed:** *Design and implement interpretable and **biologically grounded** AI-based models*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Step 1 — Install & Import"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%capture\n",
    "!pip install biopython gffpandas requests tqdm scipy matplotlib seaborn pandas numpy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import requests, os, gzip\n",
    "from tqdm.notebook import tqdm\n",
    "from scipy.stats import fisher_exact\n",
    "from statsmodels.stats.multitest import multipletests\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 120\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "print('✅ Libraries loaded.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📥 Step 2 — Reload Project 1 Results\n",
    "\n",
    "We load the GWAS results and SHAP importance tables saved in Project 1.  \n",
    "If you don't have them, re-run Project 1 first and make sure `gwas_results_DTF.csv` and `shap_importance_DTF.csv` are in your Colab working directory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Load GWAS results ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "gwas_df = pd.read_csv('gwas_results_DTF.csv')\n",
    "print(f'GWAS results loaded: {len(gwas_df):,} SNPs')\n",
    "print(gwas_df.head(3))\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Load SHAP importance ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "shap_df = pd.read_csv('shap_importance_DTF.csv')\n",
    "shap_df.columns = ['SNP', 'mean_abs_SHAP']\n",
    "print(f'\\nSHAP results loaded: {len(shap_df):,} SNPs')\n",
    "print(shap_df.head(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Define top candidates ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "BONFERRONI = 0.05 / len(gwas_df)\n",
    "N_TOP = 50\n",
    "\n",
    "gwas_top = gwas_df.nsmallest(N_TOP, 'pvalue').copy()\n",
    "shap_top = shap_df.nsmallest(N_TOP, 'mean_abs_SHAP').copy()  # smallest = we sort ascending later\n",
    "shap_top = shap_df.nlargest(N_TOP, 'mean_abs_SHAP').copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "bonferroni_hits = gwas_df[gwas_df['pvalue'] < BONFERRONI].copy()\n",
    "print(f'Bonferroni-significant SNPs : {len(bonferroni_hits)}')\n",
    "print(f'Top {N_TOP} GWAS SNPs selected')\n",
    "print(f'Top {N_TOP} SHAP SNPs selected')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Combine all candidates for annotation\n",
    "all_candidates = pd.concat([\n",
    "    gwas_top[['SNP','chrom','pos','pvalue']].assign(source='GWAS'),\n",
    "    shap_top[['SNP']].merge(gwas_df[['SNP','chrom','pos']], on='SNP', how='left').assign(pvalue=np.nan, source='SHAP')\n",
    "]).drop_duplicates(subset='SNP').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nTotal unique candidate SNPs for annotation: {len(all_candidates)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🌿 Step 3 — Download Faba Bean Reference Genome Annotation (GFF3)\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the annotation from the landmark faba bean genome paper:  \n",
    "**Jayakodi M., Golicz A.A. et al. (2023). Nature 615, 652–659.**\n",
    "\n",
    "The genome and annotation are hosted at NCBI/EBI. We download the GFF3 gene annotation file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Faba bean genome annotation — ENA/EBI accession GCA_921998355.2 (Hedin/FabMix genome)\n",
    "# Primary source: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ena/browser/view/GCA_921998355\n",
    "# We use the NCBI FTP mirror for the GFF3 annotation\n",
    "\n",
    "GFF_URL  = 'https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genomes/all/GCA/921/998/355/GCA_921998355.2_GalileoVfab1.0/GCA_921998355.2_GalileoVfab1.0_genomic.gff.gz'\n",
    "GFF_FILE = 'vfaba_genome.gff.gz'\n",
    "\n",
    "def download_file(url, filename):\n",
    "    if os.path.exists(filename):\n",
    "        print(f'  Already downloaded: {filename}')\n",
    "        return True\n",
    "    print(f'  Downloading {filename}...')\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        r = requests.get(url, stream=True, timeout=60)\n",
    "        r.raise_for_status()\n",
    "        total = int(r.headers.get('content-length', 0))\n",
    "        with open(filename, 'wb') as f, tqdm(total=total, unit='B', unit_scale=True) as bar:\n",
    "            for chunk in r.iter_content(1024*1024):\n",
    "                f.write(chunk)\n",
    "                bar.update(len(chunk))\n",
    "        print(f'  ✅ Saved: {filename}')\n",
    "        return True\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f'  ⚠️  Download failed: {e}')\n",
    "        return False\n",
    "\n",
    "success = download_file(GFF_URL, GFF_FILE)\n",
    "\n",
    "if not success:\n",
    "    print()\n",
    "    print('Alternative: Download manually from NCBI and upload to Colab:')\n",
    "    print('  https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/datasets/genome/GCA_921998355.2/')\n",
    "    print('  Then: from google.colab import files; files.upload()')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Parse GFF3: extract only gene features ─────────────────────────────────\n",
    "print('Parsing GFF3 annotation...')\n",
    "genes = []\n",
    "open_fn = gzip.open if GFF_FILE.endswith('.gz') else open\n",
    "\n",
    "with open_fn(GFF_FILE, 'rt') as f:\n",
    "    for line in f:\n",
    "        if line.startswith('#'):\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        parts = line.strip().split('\\t')\n",
    "        if len(parts) < 9:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        if parts[2] != 'gene':\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        chrom   = parts[0]\n",
    "        start   = int(parts[3])\n",
    "        end     = int(parts[4])\n",
    "        strand  = parts[6]\n",
    "        attrs   = parts[8]\n",
    "        gene_id = ''\n",
    "        gene_name = ''\n",
    "        desc = ''\n",
    "        for attr in attrs.split(';'):\n",
    "            attr = attr.strip()\n",
    "            if attr.startswith('ID='):\n",
    "                gene_id = attr[3:]\n",
    "            elif attr.startswith('Name='):\n",
    "                gene_name = attr[5:]\n",
    "            elif attr.startswith('description=') or attr.startswith('product=') or attr.startswith('Note='):\n",
    "                desc = attr.split('=', 1)[1]\n",
    "        genes.append({\n",
    "            'chrom': chrom, 'start': start, 'end': end,\n",
    "            'strand': strand, 'gene_id': gene_id,\n",
    "            'gene_name': gene_name, 'description': desc\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "gene_df = pd.DataFrame(genes)\n",
    "gene_df['midpoint'] = (gene_df['start'] + gene_df['end']) // 2\n",
    "print(f'✅ Parsed {len(gene_df):,} genes from annotation')\n",
    "print(gene_df.head(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔗 Step 4 — Map SNPs to Nearest Genes (±100 kb window)\n",
    "\n",
    "For each top SNP we find all annotated genes within 100,000 bp.  \n",
    "This is the standard approach for GWAS annotation — genes within this window are candidate regulators."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "WINDOW_BP = 100_000  # ±100 kb\n",
    "\n",
    "def find_nearby_genes(snp_chrom, snp_pos, gene_df, window=WINDOW_BP):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return genes within ±window bp of a SNP position.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if snp_pos == 0 or pd.isna(snp_pos):\n",
    "        return pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "    # Match chromosome (handle chr naming conventions)\n",
    "    chrom_str = str(snp_chrom)\n",
    "    mask_chrom = gene_df['chrom'].str.contains(chrom_str, regex=False, na=False)\n",
    "    nearby = gene_df[\n",
    "        mask_chrom &\n",
    "        (gene_df['start'] <= snp_pos + window) &\n",
    "        (gene_df['end']   >= snp_pos - window)\n",
    "    ].copy()\n",
    "    if len(nearby) > 0:\n",
    "        nearby['distance_to_snp'] = nearby['midpoint'].apply(\n",
    "            lambda m: abs(m - snp_pos)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        nearby = nearby.sort_values('distance_to_snp')\n",
    "    return nearby\n",
    "\n",
    "# Annotate all candidate SNPs\n",
    "print(f'Annotating {len(all_candidates)} candidate SNPs with ±{WINDOW_BP//1000} kb window...')\n",
    "annotation_records = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for _, snp_row in all_candidates.iterrows():\n",
    "    nearby = find_nearby_genes(snp_row['chrom'], snp_row['pos'], gene_df)\n",
    "    if len(nearby) == 0:\n",
    "        annotation_records.append({\n",
    "            'SNP': snp_row['SNP'], 'chrom': snp_row['chrom'],\n",
    "            'pos': snp_row['pos'], 'source': snp_row['source'],\n",
    "            'pvalue': snp_row['pvalue'],\n",
    "            'nearest_gene': 'No gene within window',\n",
    "            'gene_name': '', 'distance_bp': np.nan, 'description': ''\n",
    "        })\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        nearest = nearby.iloc[0]\n",
    "        annotation_records.append({\n",
    "            'SNP': snp_row['SNP'], 'chrom': snp_row['chrom'],\n",
    "            'pos': snp_row['pos'], 'source': snp_row['source'],\n",
    "            'pvalue': snp_row['pvalue'],\n",
    "            'nearest_gene': nearest['gene_id'],\n",
    "            'gene_name': nearest['gene_name'],\n",
    "            'distance_bp': nearest['distance_to_snp'],\n",
    "            'description': nearest['description']\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "annot_df = pd.DataFrame(annotation_records)\n",
    "print(f'✅ Annotation complete.')\n",
    "print(f'SNPs with a gene within window: {(annot_df[\"nearest_gene\"] != \"No gene within window\").sum()}')\n",
    "print(annot_df[['SNP','chrom','pos','source','nearest_gene','distance_bp','description']].head(10).to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🌸 Step 5 — Cross-Reference with Known Flowering-Time Genes\n",
    "\n",
    "We search for homologs of the core flowering pathway genes from Arabidopsis and legumes:\n",
    "- **FT** (FLOWERING LOCUS T) — florigen signal\n",
    "- **SOC1** — floral integrator\n",
    "- **FLC** (FLOWERING LOCUS C) — vernalization repressor\n",
    "- **CO** (CONSTANS) — photoperiod sensor\n",
    "- **LFY** (LEAFY) — floral meristem identity\n",
    "- **AP1** (APETALA1) — floral organ identity\n",
    "- **TFL1** (TERMINAL FLOWER 1) — flowering repressor\n",
    "- **SVP** (SHORT VEGETATIVE PHASE) — vernalization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "FLOWERING_GENES = [\n",
    "    'FT', 'SOC1', 'FLC', 'CONSTANS', 'CO', 'LFY', 'LEAFY',\n",
    "    'AP1', 'TFL1', 'SVP', 'VRN', 'FRI', 'GI', 'GIGANTEA',\n",
    "    'SPL', 'FUL', 'AGL', 'MAF', 'ELF', 'TOE', 'SMZ',\n",
    "    'flowering', 'floral', 'vernaliz', 'photoperiod', 'circadian'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "def flag_flowering_gene(row):\n",
    "    text = (str(row['gene_name']) + ' ' + str(row['description'])).lower()\n",
    "    for kw in FLOWERING_GENES:\n",
    "        if kw.lower() in text:\n",
    "            return kw.upper()\n",
    "    return ''\n",
    "\n",
    "annot_df['flowering_hit'] = annot_df.apply(flag_flowering_gene, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "flowering_snps = annot_df[annot_df['flowering_hit'] != '']\n",
    "print(f'SNPs near known flowering-pathway genes: {len(flowering_snps)}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "if len(flowering_snps) > 0:\n",
    "    print(flowering_snps[['SNP','chrom','source','nearest_gene','gene_name',\n",
    "                           'distance_bp','flowering_hit','description']].to_string(index=False))\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('No direct flowering gene hits — checking all annotated genes...')\n",
    "    print('Top 20 annotated SNP-proximal genes:')\n",
    "    print(annot_df[annot_df['nearest_gene'] != 'No gene within window']\n",
    "          [['SNP','source','nearest_gene','gene_name','distance_bp','description']]\n",
    "          .head(20).to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Save annotated SNP table ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "annot_df.to_csv('gwas_shap_annotated_SNPs.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print('Saved: gwas_shap_annotated_SNPs.csv')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Step 6 — Gene Ontology Enrichment Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the gene IDs proximal to our top SNPs and test for GO term enrichment using the PANTHER API (free, no registration required).\n",
    "\n",
    "This answers: **Are SNP-proximal genes enriched for biological processes related to flowering, development, or stress response?**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Collect gene IDs near top SNPs ────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "candidate_genes = annot_df[\n",
    "    annot_df['nearest_gene'] != 'No gene within window'\n",
    "]['nearest_gene'].dropna().unique().tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Unique genes near top SNPs: {len(candidate_genes)}')\n",
    "print('First 10:', candidate_genes[:10])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Also collect all genes in gene_df as the background set\n",
    "all_gene_ids = gene_df['gene_id'].dropna().unique().tolist()\n",
    "print(f'Total annotated genes (background): {len(all_gene_ids)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Fisher's exact test for keyword enrichment ────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Since PANTHER requires UniProt IDs, we do keyword-based enrichment\n",
    "# using functional descriptions from the GFF3 annotation.\n",
    "# This is a lightweight but valid alternative for a prototype analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build description corpus for background (all genes) and foreground (SNP-proximal genes)\n",
    "bg_desc   = gene_df['description'].fillna('').str.lower()\n",
    "fg_gene_ids_set = set(candidate_genes)\n",
    "fg_mask   = gene_df['gene_id'].isin(fg_gene_ids_set)\n",
    "fg_desc   = gene_df[fg_mask]['description'].fillna('').str.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "# GO-like keyword categories to test\n",
    "GO_TERMS = {\n",
    "    'Flowering / floral development' : ['flower', 'floral', 'infloresc', 'petal', 'sepal'],\n",
    "    'Vernalization / cold response'  : ['vernaliz', 'cold', 'freezing', 'frost'],\n",
    "    'Photoperiod / circadian'        : ['photoperiod', 'circadian', 'clock', 'phytochrome', 'cryptochrome'],\n",
    "    'Transcription factor'           : ['transcription factor', 'bHLH', 'MYB', 'WRKY', 'MADS', 'zinc finger'],\n",
    "    'Gibberellin / hormone signaling': ['gibberellin', 'auxin', 'cytokinin', 'ethylene', 'hormone'],\n",
    "    'Chromatin / epigenetic'         : ['histone', 'chromatin', 'methylation', 'polycomb', 'epigen'],\n",
    "    'Stress response'                : ['stress', 'defense', 'pathogen', 'drought', 'heat shock'],\n",
    "    'Kinase / signaling'             : ['kinase', 'receptor', 'signal', 'phosphatase'],\n",
    "    'Seed / storage protein'         : ['seed', 'storage', 'vicilin', 'legumin', 'albumin'],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "enrichment_results = []\n",
    "n_fg_total = len(fg_desc)\n",
    "n_bg_total = len(bg_desc)\n",
    "\n",
    "for term, keywords in GO_TERMS.items():\n",
    "    pattern = '|'.join(keywords)\n",
    "    fg_hits = fg_desc.str.contains(pattern, regex=True).sum()\n",
    "    bg_hits = bg_desc.str.contains(pattern, regex=True).sum()\n",
    "    # 2x2 contingency table\n",
    "    table = [[fg_hits, n_fg_total - fg_hits],\n",
    "             [bg_hits - fg_hits, n_bg_total - n_fg_total - (bg_hits - fg_hits)]]\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        odds, pval = fisher_exact(table, alternative='greater')\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        odds, pval = np.nan, 1.0\n",
    "    enrichment_results.append({\n",
    "        'GO_category'  : term,\n",
    "        'fg_hits'      : fg_hits,\n",
    "        'fg_total'     : n_fg_total,\n",
    "        'bg_hits'      : bg_hits,\n",
    "        'bg_total'     : n_bg_total,\n",
    "        'odds_ratio'   : round(odds, 3),\n",
    "        'pvalue'       : pval\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "enrich_df = pd.DataFrame(enrichment_results)\n",
    "# FDR correction\n",
    "_, fdr, _, _ = multipletests(enrich_df['pvalue'], method='fdr_bh')\n",
    "enrich_df['FDR'] = fdr\n",
    "enrich_df = enrich_df.sort_values('pvalue')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== GO-like Enrichment Results ===')\n",
    "print(enrich_df[['GO_category','fg_hits','fg_total','bg_hits','odds_ratio','pvalue','FDR']].to_string(index=False))\n",
    "enrich_df.to_csv('go_enrichment_results.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print('\\nSaved: go_enrichment_results.csv')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Plot enrichment ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "colors = ['#e76f51' if p < 0.05 else '#adb5bd' for p in enrich_df['FDR']]\n",
    "bars = ax.barh(\n",
    "    range(len(enrich_df)),\n",
    "    -np.log10(enrich_df['pvalue'] + 1e-10),\n",
    "    color=colors, edgecolor='white'\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_yticks(range(len(enrich_df)))\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels(enrich_df['GO_category'], fontsize=10)\n",
    "ax.axvline(-np.log10(0.05), color='red', linestyle='--', lw=1.5, label='p = 0.05')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('−log₁₀(p-value)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_title('GO-like Enrichment of SNP-Proximal Genes\\n(Days to Flowering GWAS + SHAP candidates)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "red_p = mpatches.Patch(color='#e76f51', label='FDR < 0.05')\n",
    "grey_p = mpatches.Patch(color='#adb5bd', label='Not significant')\n",
    "ax.legend(handles=[red_p, grey_p], fontsize=9)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('go_enrichment_plot.png', bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Saved: go_enrichment_plot.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🕸️ Step 7 — SNP → Gene → Pathway Visualisation\n",
    "\n",
    "We build a simple bipartite network showing:\n",
    "- Top SNPs (by GWAS + SHAP)\n",
    "- Their nearest genes\n",
    "- Colour-coded by pathway category\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the 'biologically grounded' visualisation central to the PhD's interpretable AI goal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Focus on Bonferroni-significant SNPs + top 20 SHAP SNPs for clarity\n",
    "viz_snps = pd.concat([\n",
    "    annot_df[annot_df['source'] == 'GWAS'].nsmallest(15, 'pvalue'),\n",
    "    annot_df[annot_df['source'] == 'SHAP'].head(15)\n",
    "]).drop_duplicates(subset='SNP')\n",
    "viz_snps = viz_snps[viz_snps['nearest_gene'] != 'No gene within window'].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Assign pathway colour\n",
    "def assign_color(row):\n",
    "    text = (str(row['gene_name']) + ' ' + str(row['description'])).lower()\n",
    "    if any(k in text for k in ['flower', 'floral', 'ft', 'soc1', 'lfy', 'ap1', 'tfl']):\n",
    "        return '#e76f51'  # flowering\n",
    "    elif any(k in text for k in ['transcription', 'mads', 'bhlh', 'myb', 'wrky']):\n",
    "        return '#2a9d8f'  # TF\n",
    "    elif any(k in text for k in ['kinase', 'receptor', 'signal']):\n",
    "        return '#264653'  # signaling\n",
    "    elif any(k in text for k in ['histone', 'chromatin', 'epigen']):\n",
    "        return '#e9c46a'  # epigenetic\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return '#adb5bd'  # other\n",
    "\n",
    "viz_snps['color'] = viz_snps.apply(assign_color, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, max(6, len(viz_snps) * 0.45)))\n",
    "ax.axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "n = len(viz_snps)\n",
    "snp_x, gene_x = 0.1, 0.7\n",
    "y_positions = np.linspace(0.95, 0.05, n)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, (_, row) in enumerate(viz_snps.iterrows()):\n",
    "    y = y_positions[i]\n",
    "    # SNP label\n",
    "    src_marker = '★' if row['source'] == 'GWAS' else '◆'\n",
    "    ax.text(snp_x - 0.02, y, f\"{src_marker} {row['SNP']}\",\n",
    "            ha='right', va='center', fontsize=7.5, fontfamily='monospace')\n",
    "    # Gene label\n",
    "    gene_label = row['gene_name'] if row['gene_name'] else row['nearest_gene'][:20]\n",
    "    dist_kb = f\"{row['distance_bp']/1000:.0f} kb\" if not pd.isna(row['distance_bp']) else ''\n",
    "    ax.text(gene_x + 0.02, y, f\"{gene_label}  [{dist_kb}]\",\n",
    "            ha='left', va='center', fontsize=8, color=row['color'], fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    # Connecting line\n",
    "    ax.plot([snp_x, gene_x], [y, y], color=row['color'], lw=1.2, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "    ax.scatter([snp_x], [y], color='#264653', s=30, zorder=5)\n",
    "    ax.scatter([gene_x], [y], color=row['color'], s=50, zorder=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.text(snp_x - 0.02, 1.0, 'Top SNPs\\n(★=GWAS ◆=SHAP)',\n",
    "        ha='right', fontsize=9, fontweight='bold', color='#264653')\n",
    "ax.text(gene_x + 0.02, 1.0, 'Nearest Annotated Gene',\n",
    "        ha='left', fontsize=9, fontweight='bold', color='#264653')\n",
    "\n",
    "legend_items = [\n",
    "    mpatches.Patch(color='#e76f51', label='Flowering pathway'),\n",
    "    mpatches.Patch(color='#2a9d8f', label='Transcription factor'),\n",
    "    mpatches.Patch(color='#264653', label='Signaling/kinase'),\n",
    "    mpatches.Patch(color='#e9c46a', label='Chromatin/epigenetic'),\n",
    "    mpatches.Patch(color='#adb5bd', label='Other/unknown'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "ax.legend(handles=legend_items, loc='lower center',\n",
    "          bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.04), ncol=3, fontsize=8)\n",
    "ax.set_title('SNP → Nearest Gene Network\\n(Biologically Grounded Annotation of DTF Candidates)',\n",
    "             fontsize=12, pad=20)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('snp_gene_network.png', bbox_inches='tight', dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Saved: snp_gene_network.png')"
   ]
